From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Latin resuscitāre.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /resuθiˈtaɾ/ [re.su.θiˈt̪aɾ] (Spain)
  • IPA(key): /resusiˈtaɾ/ [re.su.siˈt̪aɾ] (Latin America, Philippines)
  • Audio (Colombia):(file)
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: re‧su‧ci‧tar

Verb

[edit]

resucitar (first-person singular present resucito, first-person singular preterite resucité, past participle resucitado)

  1. to resuscitate
